# UI Standards — Emil Design Engineering

Apply these principles to ALL UI work in this repo. Reference the full skill at ~/.cursor/skills/emil-design-engineering/.

## Forms & Inputs
- Wrap inputs in `<form>` so Enter submits
- Support Cmd+Enter / Ctrl+Enter for textarea submission
- Disable buttons after submission to prevent duplicates
- Use `spellCheck={false}` and `autoComplete="off"` on non-standard text inputs
- Font size 16px+ on inputs to prevent iOS zoom (shadcn handles this)
- Labels must be associated with inputs via `htmlFor`/`id`

## Layout & Typography
- No layout shift: use hardcoded dimensions, `tabular-nums` for changing numbers
- Never change font weight on hover/selected states
- Use `text-wrap: balance` on headings

## Animations & Transitions
- Never use `transition: all` — specify exact properties
- Enter/exit: `ease-out`, 150-250ms
- Movement: `ease-in-out`
- Hover/color: `ease`
- Every animation needs `prefers-reduced-motion` support
- Don't animate things users see 100+ times daily

## Touch & Accessibility
- 44px minimum tap targets
- Hover effects only via `@media (hover: hover) and (pointer: fine)`
- Every icon button needs `aria-label`
- Keyboard navigation must work: tab order, focus management
- `touch-action: manipulation` on buttons/links to prevent double-tap zoom

## Performance
- Only animate `transform` and `opacity`
- Avoid blur filters > 20px
- Pause looping animations when off-screen
- Virtualize lists with > ~50 items
